WEBVTT

00:10.567 --> 00:11.765
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "GREENLEAF"...</i>

00:11.767 --> 00:13.465
YOU'VE GOT TO GIVE ME
SOMETHING ON GRACE,

00:13.467 --> 00:15.365
SOMETHING BIG
AND SOON,

00:15.367 --> 00:17.632
OR NEITHER ONE OF US
ARE GONNA PREACH AT THIS CHURCH.

00:17.634 --> 00:18.932
YOU WANTED TO KNOW
WHO'S THE MONEY BEHIND

00:18.934 --> 00:20.165
CITY ON A HILL, RIGHT?

00:20.167 --> 00:21.165
WERE YOU ABLE TO FIND OUT?

00:21.167 --> 00:22.498
IT'S HARMONY & HOPE.

00:22.500 --> 00:23.932
Is that gonna be a problem?

00:23.934 --> 00:25.265
Jacob:
GOODBYE, LAND.

00:25.267 --> 00:27.531
HELLO, DREAM HOUSE.

00:29.000 --> 00:33.132
YOU ARE AN OLD RUSTY JALOPY
WITH A CORPSE IN THE TRUCK.

00:33.134 --> 00:34.399
AAH!

00:34.401 --> 00:36.332
Jacob: DANTE GOT OUT OF LINE.
WAY OUT.

00:36.334 --> 00:38.398
I GOT FIRED
BY THE RED DEVILS.

00:38.400 --> 00:40.000
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO WAIT
ON THAT HOUSE.

00:41.067 --> 00:42.465
Sophia: DON'T WORRY.
HE TOLD ME ABOUT YOUR DEAL

00:42.467 --> 00:43.865
AND HOW HE'S SUPPOSED TO
STAY IN THE DARK

00:43.867 --> 00:45.065
LIKE SOME KIND OF SECRET

00:45.067 --> 00:46.265
UNTIL YOU SAY IT'S COOL
TO COME OUT.

00:46.267 --> 00:47.598
I GET IT.
I WON'T TELL.

00:47.600 --> 00:50.132
I'M LOW ON CASH.

00:50.134 --> 00:51.532
DIDN'T I
JUST GIVE YOU MONEY?

00:51.534 --> 00:54.132
- WE'RE DONE.
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN WE'RE DONE?

00:54.134 --> 00:57.532
THE NEXT PERSON THAT ASKS ME
WHO I AM, I'M TELLING THEM.

00:57.534 --> 00:58.698
I NEED YOUR HELP
WITH SOMETHING,

00:58.700 --> 01:01.199
AND I'M A LITTLE
MYSTIFIED MYSELF.

01:01.201 --> 01:02.732
WHAT IS IT?

01:02.734 --> 01:03.734
MY SON.

01:07.267 --> 01:09.332
DON'T YOU HAVE
ANYTHING TO SAY?

01:09.334 --> 01:11.798
I JUST TOLD YOU
I HAVE A GROWN SON.

01:11.800 --> 01:13.532
DO YOU HAVE A PICTURE?

01:13.534 --> 01:15.199
LET'S SEE.

01:18.001 --> 01:20.398
YEAH.

01:23.467 --> 01:25.665
HERE. LOOK.

01:25.667 --> 01:27.098
HERE'S ONE.

01:27.100 --> 01:29.898
OH.

01:34.801 --> 01:38.465
WHAT A SAD, DIFFICULT STORY
FOR YOU, FOR HIM, FOR NOAH.

01:40.400 --> 01:42.232
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE.

01:42.234 --> 01:44.299
HASN'T BEEN SIMPLE.
THAT'S FOR SURE.

01:46.234 --> 01:48.732
ESPECIALLY FOR NOAH.

01:53.067 --> 01:55.198
AND AS FOR YOU
KEEPING THIS FROM ME,

01:55.200 --> 01:58.831
THIS MOST RECENT CHAPTER
SPECIFICALLY,

01:58.833 --> 02:00.499
I HAVE TO
ASK YOU THIS.

02:00.501 --> 02:02.031
HAVE YOU PRAYED
ABOUT IT?

02:02.033 --> 02:04.432
OF COURSE I PRAYED ABOUT IT,
MAMA.

02:04.434 --> 02:05.432
WHERE'S A.J. NOW?

02:05.434 --> 02:08.365
AT THE MOMENT,
I'M NOT SURE.

02:08.366 --> 02:09.632
HE HASN'T RETURNED
MY CALLS

02:09.633 --> 02:11.165
SINCE WE HAD THE ARGUMENT
ABOUT THE MONEY.

02:11.167 --> 02:12.765
AND DID YOU TELL SOPHIA

02:12.767 --> 02:14.365
THAT YOU WERE GOING TO
SPEAK TO ME ABOUT THIS?

02:14.367 --> 02:15.565
NOT YET. I WILL.

02:15.567 --> 02:17.598
HOPEFULLY, THAT WILL SATISFY
HER CONDITIONS

02:17.600 --> 02:20.132
FOR RETURNING HOME

02:20.134 --> 02:22.531
AT LEAST
EVEN ONLY FOR A VISIT.

02:24.200 --> 02:26.399
- IT'S OKAY. MARICEL?
- YES, MA'AM?

02:26.401 --> 02:29.365
Charity:
CAN YOU HELP ME, PLEASE?

02:29.367 --> 02:32.098
SO, MAY I MEET
MY NEW GRANDSON?

02:32.100 --> 02:34.665
IF I CAN GET
AHOLD OF HIM, YEAH.

02:36.300 --> 02:38.498
WHAT ARE WE GONNA TELL
THE CHURCH?

02:38.500 --> 02:39.799
EXCUSE ME?

02:39.801 --> 02:41.899
THE ONLY REASON
THAT I AM IN THE POSITION

02:41.901 --> 02:43.498
THAT I AM IN RIGHT NOW
IS BECAUSE

02:43.500 --> 02:45.965
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE THE GREENLEAF
WITH ALL THE MORALS.

02:45.967 --> 02:47.965
IN THIS DAY AND AGE,

02:47.967 --> 02:49.998
THERE'S NO REAL SHAME
IN GIVING UP A CHILD,

02:50.000 --> 02:51.265
AND THE WAY YOU HANDLED IT

02:51.267 --> 02:53.598
WHEN YOU REACHED OUT TO YOU
WHEN HE CAME OF AGE,

02:53.600 --> 02:58.065
WELL, THAT WAS
SLIGHTLY LESS ADORABLE,

02:58.067 --> 03:02.465
BUT HIS PRISON RECORD
IS A THING OF THE PAST.

03:03.701 --> 03:09.065
♪♪

03:09.067 --> 03:14.132
♪♪

03:14.134 --> 03:15.399
WHAT HAPPENED NOW?

03:21.267 --> 03:28.465
♪♪

03:28.467 --> 03:31.231
THIS HAS TO BE KEPT
IN THE FAMILY.

03:31.233 --> 03:33.032
WHO ELSE
WOULD I TELL?

03:36.967 --> 03:38.665
♪ AMEN ♪

03:41.167 --> 03:42.498
♪ ALL RIGHT ♪

03:42.500 --> 03:43.698
♪ AMEN ♪

03:43.700 --> 03:46.632
♪ UH-HUH, HMM ♪

03:46.634 --> 03:49.199
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH ♪

03:52.467 --> 03:53.665
♪ WELL ♪

03:57.067 --> 04:00.198
♪ OH-OHH, OHH ♪

04:00.200 --> 04:05.532
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

04:05.534 --> 04:08.599
♪ AMEN, AMEN ♪
♪ OH ♪

04:12.067 --> 04:13.865
♪ YEAH ♪

04:13.867 --> 04:16.865
<font color="#ffff00">Captions by VITAC</font>...
<font color="#00ffff">www.vitac.com</font>

04:16.867 --> 04:19.865
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

04:19.867 --> 04:25.465
♪♪

04:25.467 --> 04:30.665
A.J., HEY, IT'S ME...
AGAIN.

04:30.667 --> 04:33.998
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET
WITH ME ABOUT THE MONEY, OKAY,

04:34.000 --> 04:36.332
AND I'M SORRY.

04:36.334 --> 04:39.265
JUST PLEASE CALL ME BACK.

04:39.267 --> 04:44.665
I TOLD THE FAMILY ABOUT YOU,
AND THEY WANT TO MEET YOU...

04:44.667 --> 04:46.065
TONIGHT, IF POSSIBLE.

04:50.200 --> 04:52.832
OKAY. BYE.

04:56.334 --> 04:58.798
I FEEL LIKE A...

04:58.800 --> 05:03.932
A SQUIRREL ON A BRANCH
ON THE FARTHEST DRY END

05:03.934 --> 05:07.399
AND OF A THIN, BARE BRANCH.

05:07.401 --> 05:09.065
JAMES,
ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?

05:09.067 --> 05:12.332
NO, NOT REALLY, DEAR.
NO.

05:12.334 --> 05:16.798
WELL, WHAT HAS YOU
SO TRANSFIXED?

05:16.800 --> 05:21.398
I'M THINKING ABOUT A NIGHT
YEARS AGO,

05:21.400 --> 05:24.665
ABOUT A WEEK
AFTER GIGI LEFT HOME.

05:24.667 --> 05:27.198
SHE CALLED.

05:27.200 --> 05:30.198
NEEDED MONEY.

05:30.200 --> 05:35.265
I SAID I'D COME UP TO CHICAGO,
AND I'D BRING HER BACK.

05:35.267 --> 05:37.599
SHE SAID NO.

05:37.601 --> 05:43.798
I'D ALWAYS PICTURED HER
ON THE OTHER END OF THAT LINE,

05:43.800 --> 05:46.598
OBSTINATE,
RIGHTEOUS, PROUD.

05:46.600 --> 05:52.299
NOW I KNOW SHE WAS PREGNANT,
SCARED, AND LONELY.

05:54.334 --> 05:58.065
IF ONLY I'D HAVE GONE UP THERE
AND BROUGHT HER HOME.

05:59.400 --> 06:02.165
MAYBE NONE OF THIS
WOULD HAVE HAPPENED.

06:02.167 --> 06:07.498
OUR JOB NOW IS TO GRAFT HIM
INTO THE FAMILY,

06:07.500 --> 06:10.298
AND PUT HIM WHERE THE SON
CAN DO HIM SOME GOOD.

06:10.300 --> 06:17.031
♪♪

06:20.500 --> 06:22.432
OH.

06:22.434 --> 06:24.665
UM, MORNING, PASTOR.

06:24.667 --> 06:27.932
I WAS JUST, UM...
I WAS WATCHING A SERMON

06:27.934 --> 06:29.265
- MM-HMM.
- MM-HMM.

06:29.267 --> 06:30.498
AND BY SERMON,
YOU MEAN THE FIGHT

06:30.500 --> 06:32.432
BETWEEN ME
AND HALF THE RED DEVILS.

06:32.434 --> 06:34.232
I WAS JUST
READING THE COMMENTS.

06:34.234 --> 06:35.599
YEAH.

06:36.734 --> 06:37.998
WHAT'S
THE INTERNET SAYING?

06:38.000 --> 06:39.465
IT'S CALLING YOU
PASTOR HOLYFIELD.

06:39.467 --> 06:43.298
NICE.

06:43.300 --> 06:44.898
PHIL IN HIS OFFICE?
- YEAH.

06:44.900 --> 06:46.565
I'LL LET HIM KNOW YOU'RE HERE.
- ALRIGHT.

06:46.567 --> 06:47.965
JUST, UH,
HAVE HIM CALL ME.

06:47.967 --> 06:49.698
- OKAY.
- THANKS.

07:02.367 --> 07:03.932
- STAND UP.
- WHY?

07:03.934 --> 07:06.198
UGH, JUST DO IT, PLEASE.

07:08.267 --> 07:13.998
♪♪

07:14.000 --> 07:14.798
WHAT?

07:14.800 --> 07:16.398
YOU'RE GONNA NEED
TO SIT DOWN.

07:16.400 --> 07:17.932
CHARITY, COME ON.
I JUST STOOD UP.

07:17.934 --> 07:19.665
I KNOW, BUT I'VE ALWAYS
WANT TO SAY THAT,

07:19.667 --> 07:21.532
AND NOW
IS THE PERFECT TIME.

07:21.534 --> 07:22.498
WHAT'S GOING ON?

07:22.500 --> 07:24.732
SIT DOWN,
AND I'LL TELL YOU.

07:28.600 --> 07:29.532
WELL?

07:29.534 --> 07:31.099
GRACE HAS
A SECRET SON.

07:34.001 --> 07:36.998
- YOUR FAMILY...
- CAREFUL.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.265
GO ON.

07:38.267 --> 07:40.265
SHE HAD A BABY
RIGHT AFTER SHE LEFT HOME

07:40.267 --> 07:41.599
SHE NEVER TOLD
ANYBODY ABOUT,

07:41.601 --> 07:44.465
AND SHE JUST GAVE HIM UP
FOR ADOPTION.

07:44.467 --> 07:46.665
- WHO'S THE FATHER?
- NOAH.

07:46.667 --> 07:48.532
SO THAT'S WHY
HE CAME TO VISIT.

07:48.534 --> 07:51.998
AND WHY HE AND ISABEL
BROKE UP.

07:52.000 --> 07:53.665
ISN'T THIS LIKE
THE SILVER BULLET?

07:53.667 --> 07:54.865
WELL, IT'S SOMETHING.

07:54.867 --> 07:57.299
I'M NOT SURE IF IT'S A BULLET,
A BLANK, OR A TRAP.

07:57.301 --> 07:59.531
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
THE GOOD ONE, PHIL.

07:59.533 --> 08:00.865
SHE TURNED HER BACK
ON THAT CHILD

08:00.867 --> 08:03.399
WHEN HE TRIED TO CONNECT...
HER SON.

08:03.401 --> 08:05.365
IT'S NOT LIKE
SHE HAD AN ABORTION.

08:07.234 --> 08:09.632
YEAH, I THOUGHT ABOUT
THAT, TOO.

08:09.634 --> 08:12.498
DID I TELL YOU
HE'S AN EX-CON?

08:12.500 --> 08:13.832
SERIOUSLY?

08:13.834 --> 08:16.098
HE DID FIVE YEARS
FOR BURGLARY.

08:16.100 --> 08:17.998
EH, IT'S MORE ABOUT HIM
THAN HER.

08:19.734 --> 08:21.332
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

08:21.334 --> 08:24.931
I'M JUST TRYING TO SEE HOW WE
CAN REALLY USE THIS AGAINST HER.

08:24.933 --> 08:26.265
IS THERE ANY CHANCE
YOU COULD SPEAK TO HIM,

08:26.267 --> 08:28.132
YOU KNOW, GET A SENSE
OF HIS POINT OF VIEW

08:28.134 --> 08:30.132
WHEN IT COMES TO HIS MOTHER?
- MAYBE.

08:30.134 --> 08:32.664
HE MIGHT BE COMING OVER
FOR DINNER TONIGHT...

08:32.667 --> 08:34.732
IF GIGI CAN FIND HIM.

08:34.734 --> 08:35.664
WHAT, HE'S LOST?

08:35.667 --> 08:37.865
NO.

08:37.866 --> 08:39.030
HE'S MAD AT HER.

08:39.033 --> 08:42.532
MM.
WELL, THAT'S PROMISING.

08:42.534 --> 08:44.832
AND I DIDN'T EVEN
HAVE TO SNOOP.

08:48.334 --> 08:49.732
WHAT?

08:49.734 --> 08:51.632
YOUR HAIR.

08:51.634 --> 08:53.365
LOOKS NICE TODAY.

08:53.367 --> 08:54.367
DOES IT?

08:57.867 --> 08:59.199
THANKS.

09:04.000 --> 09:07.398
OH, HEY, JACOB. HI.

09:07.400 --> 09:10.398
- WHAT HAPPENED?
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

09:10.400 --> 09:11.865
ARE YOU IN TROUBLE
WITH PHIL, TOO?

09:11.867 --> 09:13.198
WHY WOULD I
BE IN TROUBLE?

09:13.200 --> 09:15.198
YOU JUST CAME OUT
OF HIS OFFICE.

09:15.200 --> 09:17.099
OH. WELL, YEAH.

09:17.101 --> 09:19.498
I MEAN, ACCORDING TO PHIL,
I'M ALWAYS IN TROUBLE.

09:19.500 --> 09:20.965
I'M THE PROBLEM CHILD.

09:22.567 --> 09:24.032
WHAT'D YOU DO?

09:24.034 --> 09:25.732
WHAT?

09:25.734 --> 09:28.132
I CALLED JUDEE WHITMORE,
AND I TOLD HER

09:28.134 --> 09:31.532
WE ARE NEVER SINGING
THAT WELCOME SONG AGAIN... EVER.

09:31.534 --> 09:34.065
OKAY, BUT, UH,
I COULD'VE SWORN

09:34.067 --> 09:36.132
I JUST HEARD CARLTON
AND THE CHOIR PRACTICING IT,

09:36.134 --> 09:37.798
AND IT SOUNDED LIKE
A NEW ARRANGEMENT.

09:37.800 --> 09:40.532
YEAH, THEY'RE DUMB,
BUT, JACOB, I GOT TO GO.

09:40.534 --> 09:41.732
PHIL IS SO MAD AT ME.

09:41.734 --> 09:43.832
BUT GOD IS GOOD.

09:49.934 --> 09:55.065
Choir: ♪ WELCOME TO THE FAMILY
OF GOD ♪

09:55.067 --> 09:58.398
Woman: ♪ WELCOME TO THE FAMILY
OF GOD ♪

10:05.667 --> 10:07.732
HELLO? THIS IS
PASTOR GRACE GREENLEAF.

10:07.734 --> 10:10.532
HEY. IT'S A.J.

10:10.534 --> 10:12.232
I'VE BEEN ARRESTED.

10:21.600 --> 10:28.265
♪♪

10:28.267 --> 10:29.599
A.J. DELAJAE.

10:29.601 --> 10:30.865
SIGN RIGHT HERE.

10:30.867 --> 10:32.099
OH, THANK YOU.

10:34.934 --> 10:36.332
- OKAY.
- THANK YOU.

10:39.934 --> 10:41.599
HE'S JUST INSIDE.

10:48.467 --> 10:50.799
You got to say I was with you.

10:52.300 --> 10:53.698
You want me to lie?

10:53.700 --> 10:56.265
Last night, from like 10:00
to like midnight,

10:56.267 --> 10:58.665
you got to say you were with me
at my place, pastoring me.

10:58.667 --> 11:00.132
Where exactly were you?

11:00.134 --> 11:01.865
At my place,
but I can't prove it.

11:04.567 --> 11:05.965
You did come to the church
yesterday,

11:05.967 --> 11:07.298
asking for more money.

11:07.300 --> 11:10.865
Yeah, maybe forget that part,
okay?

11:10.867 --> 11:13.398
Your boy Aaron says you would do
anything for a stranger.

11:13.400 --> 11:17.065
Just pretend I'm a stranger.

11:17.067 --> 11:19.865
I can't go back to jail again.

11:19.867 --> 11:21.065
Please.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.732
Promise me you didn't do it.

11:26.734 --> 11:28.531
I didn't.

11:28.533 --> 11:30.398
They're just looking for
someone to pin this on,

11:30.400 --> 11:33.532
and I fit the description.

11:33.534 --> 11:36.665
You got to help me.
Please.

11:36.667 --> 11:41.931
♪♪

11:41.933 --> 11:47.098
♪♪

11:47.100 --> 11:48.998
I WAS <i> BREAKING UP</i> A FIGHT.

11:49.000 --> 11:52.598
JACOB, I'VE DEVOTED ALMOST
AN HOUR TO THIS CONVERSATION.

11:52.600 --> 11:53.998
IT'S OVER.

11:54.000 --> 11:55.599
YOU KNOW THIS IS
MY FAMILY'S CHURCH, RIGHT?

11:55.601 --> 11:57.865
YOUR FAMILY IS THIS CHURCH'S
BIGGEST PROBLEM.

11:57.867 --> 11:58.732
IT ALWAYS HAS BEEN.

11:58.734 --> 12:00.398
JUST ADMIT
YOU SCREWED UP.

12:00.400 --> 12:02.532
JUST ADMIT YOU TAKE
A SPECIFIC PLEASURE

12:02.534 --> 12:05.332
IN TRYING TO REMOVE ME
FROM A PLACE I BELONG.

12:05.334 --> 12:07.199
I MEAN, WHAT'S UP
WITH THAT, HUH?

12:07.201 --> 12:08.465
WHAT'S YOUR DEAL WITH ME?

12:08.467 --> 12:10.799
I HAVE NO DEAL WITH YOU.

12:10.801 --> 12:12.465
BOB SAW THE NEWS.
BOB WANTS YOU OUT.

12:12.467 --> 12:14.499
BOB SAID TO MAKE IT HAPPEN
FULL STOP.

12:14.501 --> 12:15.965
SHOULD WE GET HIM
ON THE PHONE?

12:21.200 --> 12:22.598
I'M GONNA SAY NO,

12:22.600 --> 12:24.865
BUT ONLY BECAUSE I DON'T WANT
TO MAKE TROUBLE FOR GRACE.

12:24.867 --> 12:25.732
WELL, I THINK THAT'S WISE,

12:25.734 --> 12:26.865
CONSIDERING SHE STUCK
HER NECK OUT

12:26.867 --> 12:28.865
TO GET YOU THIS JOB
YOU NEVER FOUND IMPORTANT ENOUGH

12:28.867 --> 12:30.865
TO MAKE
YOUR FIRST PRIORITY.

12:30.867 --> 12:32.765
YOU KNOW WHAT?

12:32.767 --> 12:35.865
YOU BETTER LEAVE BEFORE
I DO SOMETHING YOU REGRET.

12:38.034 --> 12:39.965
JACOB.

12:39.967 --> 12:42.231
PHIL, CAREFUL.

12:42.233 --> 12:45.832
NOT EVERY SON
OF A PREACHER'S ANOINTED.

12:45.834 --> 12:47.832
SOME ARE JUST CHILDREN.

12:50.067 --> 12:52.565
I THINK THIS COULD BE
A REAL TURNING POINT.

13:01.334 --> 13:08.998
♪♪

13:15.267 --> 13:18.732
SAME CLOTHING,
SAME BUILD,

13:18.734 --> 13:21.131
AND HIS PRINTS
WERE ON THE COUNTER.

13:21.133 --> 13:23.099
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

13:23.101 --> 13:24.965
WE'RE SURE
THEY'RE HIS PRINTS.

13:24.967 --> 13:26.832
THAT BEING SAID,
HE'S A REGULAR CUSTOMER.

13:26.834 --> 13:29.031
HE MIGHT HAVE
BEEN THERE EARLIER.

13:29.033 --> 13:32.032
HE MIGHT HAVE BEEN
CASING THE PLACE.

13:32.034 --> 13:35.832
BUT AT THIS POINT,
THAT'S KIND OF UP TO YOU.

13:35.834 --> 13:36.932
HOW'S THAT UP TO ME?

13:36.934 --> 13:38.598
WELL, MR. DELAJAE SAYS
THAT HE WAS WITH YOU

13:38.600 --> 13:40.899
WHEN THE SURVEILLANCE
WAS TAKEN.

13:40.901 --> 13:42.532
WAS HE?

13:44.534 --> 13:46.199
YOU SAY YES,
HE'S FREE TO GO.

13:48.800 --> 13:50.032
ACTUALLY,
HANG ON A SEC.

13:51.601 --> 13:53.265
OKAY IF I RECORD THIS,
PASTOR?

13:53.267 --> 13:55.532
- OF COURSE.
- YOU PROBABLY REMEMBER THIS

13:55.534 --> 13:56.798
FROM WHEN YOU WERE IN HERE
LAST YEAR

13:56.800 --> 13:59.332
FOR THE SITUATION
WITH YOUR UNCLE.

14:00.600 --> 14:02.332
INTERVIEWING
PASTOR GRACE GREENLEAF

14:02.334 --> 14:06.132
REGARDING A.J. DELAJAE.

14:06.134 --> 14:07.398
UH, THE ACCUSED SAYS
THAT HE WAS WITH YOU

14:07.400 --> 14:08.198
WHEN THIS VIDEO WAS TAKEN.

14:08.200 --> 14:09.200
WAS HE?

14:16.733 --> 14:20.532
YEAH, I WAS WITH HIM LAST NIGHT
FROM ABOUT 9:30 TO MIDNIGHT.

14:20.534 --> 14:22.365
- WHERE?
- AT HIS APARTMENT.

14:22.367 --> 14:24.499
YOU MAKE A LOT OF LATE-NIGHT
CALLS IN YOUR LINE OF BUSINESS?

14:24.501 --> 14:26.531
- NO, BUT HE WAS RECENTLY...
- RELEASED FROM PRISON.

14:26.533 --> 14:29.432
WE KNOW.
- IT'S A CHALLENGING TIME.

14:29.434 --> 14:31.265
WE'RE ALSO AWARE OF THE FACT,
PASTOR GREENLEAF,

14:31.267 --> 14:33.965
THAT YOU PLAYED A PIVOTAL ROLE
IN THE MODIFICATION

14:33.967 --> 14:36.232
OF MR. DELAJAE'S
PAROLE AGREEMENT,

14:36.234 --> 14:38.032
WHICH ALLOWED HIM
TO LEAVE ARIZONA.

14:38.034 --> 14:39.365
THAT'S CORRECT.

14:39.367 --> 14:41.598
DID YOU KNOW HIM FROM BEFORE,
WHEN YOU WERE IN PHOENIX?

14:41.600 --> 14:42.699
SORT OF.

14:46.100 --> 14:47.365
I, UM...

14:48.934 --> 14:50.798
I'M HIS MOTHER.

14:50.800 --> 14:53.365
- INTERESTING.
- HIS BIOLOGICAL MOTHER.

14:53.367 --> 14:54.665
I'M SURE THERE'S
A REAL STORY THERE.

14:54.667 --> 14:56.198
MM-HMM.

14:56.200 --> 14:57.965
SO, ARE YOU PREPARED TO SIGN
A SWORN STATEMENT

14:57.967 --> 15:00.932
SAYING THAT YOU WERE WITH
MR. DELAJAE AT HIS APARTMENT

15:00.934 --> 15:02.599
AT THE TIME
THE CRIME WAS COMMITTED?

15:06.400 --> 15:07.665
I AM.

15:07.667 --> 15:11.131
YOU UNDERSTAND LYING TO A
POLICE OFFICER'S A CRIME, RIGHT?

15:11.133 --> 15:12.265
I DO.

15:14.700 --> 15:15.865
OKAY.

15:17.767 --> 15:19.798
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

15:19.800 --> 15:25.765
♪♪

15:25.767 --> 15:27.965
HERE'S YOUR CHECK,
MS. GREENLEAF.

15:27.967 --> 15:29.765
THANK YOU, MR. AMABLE.

15:33.134 --> 15:36.932
AND THAT CONCLUDES
OUR BUSINESS.

15:36.934 --> 15:38.698
UNLESS THERE'S
SOMETHING ELSE.

15:38.700 --> 15:40.565
I KNOW
YOU'RE HARMONY & HOPE.

15:40.567 --> 15:42.332
WE'RE AN INDEPENDENT LLC.

15:42.334 --> 15:45.732
THAT'S COMPLETELY FUNDED
BY H&H.

15:45.734 --> 15:48.465
AND THIS TROUBLES YOU
FOR SOME REASON?

15:48.467 --> 15:49.865
NO.

15:49.867 --> 15:50.932
NOT AT ALL.

15:50.934 --> 15:52.731
IT INTERESTS ME.

15:52.733 --> 15:56.932
IT INTERESTS ME
TO WONDER WHAT H&H IS UP TO

15:56.934 --> 15:59.965
BY HIDING
ITS IDENTITY FROM US.

15:59.967 --> 16:01.498
I SEE.

16:01.500 --> 16:03.632
HOW MUCH
IS IT WORTH TO YOU

16:03.634 --> 16:07.365
THAT NO ONE AT CALVARY
FINDS OUT ABOUT THIS?

16:07.367 --> 16:09.965
KERISSA.
MAY I CALL YOU KERISSA?

16:09.967 --> 16:11.932
JUST TELL ME
HOW MUCH IT'S WORTH.

16:11.934 --> 16:14.565
YOU DON'T LOOK VERY HAPPY
RIGHT NOW.

16:14.567 --> 16:16.232
WELL,
I'LL CALL MY HUSBAND.

16:16.234 --> 16:19.332
IF YOU HAVEN'T TOLD HIM
THAT YOU KNOW THIS ALREADY,

16:19.334 --> 16:20.865
YOU MUST HAVE
YOUR REASONS.

16:20.867 --> 16:23.065
BUT GO AHEAD.

16:23.067 --> 16:24.465
CALL HIM.

16:29.267 --> 16:31.265
MY MOTHER-IN-LAW
IS DRIVING ME CRAZY,

16:31.267 --> 16:33.332
MY HUSBAND JUST LOST
BOTH OF HIS JOBS,

16:33.334 --> 16:35.198
I NEED TO BUY A HOUSE,

16:35.200 --> 16:37.065
AND THE CHECK
THAT YOU JUST GAVE ME

16:37.067 --> 16:40.199
ISN'T EVEN HALF OF THE MONEY
I NEED TO BUY IT.

16:45.167 --> 16:46.732
I'M SORRY.
- IT'S OKAY.

16:49.600 --> 16:53.265
TO BE CLEAR,
WERE CALVARY TO HEAR

16:53.267 --> 16:55.198
THAT WE BOUGHT
YOUR LAND,

16:55.200 --> 16:58.265
IT WOULD MAKE THINGS
HARDER,

16:58.267 --> 16:59.832
BUT NOT MUCH.

17:08.733 --> 17:11.065
SHALL I MAKE IT OUT TO YOU
OR YOUR HUSBAND?

17:11.067 --> 17:13.598
EITHER WORKS.

17:15.599 --> 17:16.932
YOU CAN MAKE IT OUT TO ME.

17:28.166 --> 17:30.898
THAT BEING SAID,

17:30.900 --> 17:33.832
TO SHARE THIS INFORMATION NOW
WOULD BE BAD FORM.

17:35.834 --> 17:40.265
AT LEAST,
AFTER RECEIVING THIS.

17:42.067 --> 17:44.299
UNDERSTOOD.

17:45.867 --> 17:46.865
THANK YOU.

17:46.867 --> 17:48.398
MAY I SEE YOU AGAIN?

17:49.734 --> 17:52.598
FOR WHAT?

17:52.600 --> 17:55.998
IT SEEMS
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE

17:56.000 --> 17:57.865
GIVING YOU HALF
OF WHAT YOU NEED.

17:57.867 --> 17:59.532
I'D LIKE TO SEE
WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE

17:59.534 --> 18:02.065
WHEN SOMEONE GIVES YOU
ALL OF IT.

18:02.067 --> 18:03.532
NOW,
IF YOU WERE MINE,

18:03.534 --> 18:06.065
YOU'D NEVER HAVE TO DO
SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

18:06.067 --> 18:08.632
I'D BE SURE YOU WERE
ALWAYS TAKING CARE OF.

18:12.800 --> 18:13.932
MAYBE...

18:13.934 --> 18:16.665
MM.

18:16.667 --> 18:18.798
AFTER
THE CHECK CLEARS.

18:18.800 --> 18:26.800
♪♪

18:32.434 --> 18:33.565
THANKS FOR DOING THAT.

18:33.567 --> 18:34.898
AFTER THIS LITTLE DINNER,

18:34.900 --> 18:36.598
OR WHATEVER YOUR GRANDMOTHER'S
GOT PLANNED THIS EVENING,

18:36.600 --> 18:38.865
WE'RE GONNA SIT DOWN AND WE'RE
GONNA HAVE A VERY LONG TALK.

18:38.867 --> 18:39.798
THIS IS NOT WORKING.

18:39.800 --> 18:41.032
I DIDN'T DO IT.

18:41.034 --> 18:43.465
YEAH I KNOW,
BUT I JUST LIED TO THE POLICE.

18:43.467 --> 18:46.499
THAT IS NOT IDEAL.

18:46.501 --> 18:48.698
A-ARE YOU GONNA
TELL THEM?

18:48.700 --> 18:50.965
YOUR MOM?
YOUR FAMILY?

18:50.967 --> 18:53.765
WHAT, THAT YOU JUST GOT ARRESTED
FOR ROBBING A PHARMACY

18:53.767 --> 18:57.132
AND I HAD TO LIE UNDER OATH
TO GET YOU RELEASED?

18:57.134 --> 18:58.998
NO, I'M NOT GONNA
LEAD WITH THAT.

19:07.634 --> 19:15.634
♪♪

19:16.500 --> 19:24.500
♪♪

19:26.867 --> 19:28.732
Kerissa:
HELLO, HANDSOME.

19:28.734 --> 19:30.732
HEY.

19:30.734 --> 19:31.799
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT YOU.

19:31.801 --> 19:34.465
AWW. IS THAT SO?
AND HERE I AM.

19:34.467 --> 19:36.165
WHAT A COINCIDENCE.

19:36.167 --> 19:37.298
WHY AREN'T YOU AT WORK?

19:37.300 --> 19:39.632
WELL, I CAME TO TAKE
MY HUBBY OUT.

19:39.634 --> 19:40.632
WELL,
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

19:40.634 --> 19:42.598
I'M SURE IT'S NOT ME
GETTING FIRED

19:42.600 --> 19:44.265
ONE MORE TIME
FROM CALVARY.

19:46.000 --> 19:48.398
WELL...

19:48.400 --> 19:50.798
WE PUT AN OFFER IN
ON THE HOUSE.

19:50.800 --> 19:51.965
WHICH HOUSE?

19:51.967 --> 19:52.899
THE ONE
THAT WE'VE BEEN LOOKING AT.

19:52.901 --> 19:54.298
THE ONE THAT I LOVE.

19:54.300 --> 19:56.165
- OKAY, WAIT...
- WE PUT AN OFFER IN.

19:56.167 --> 19:57.098
WITH WHAT MONEY?

19:57.100 --> 19:59.098
THE MONEY FROM THE LAND.

19:59.100 --> 20:00.332
I THOUGHT
WE DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH.

20:00.334 --> 20:02.832
WELL, I JUST SCRAPED UP
A COUPLE OF MORE DOLLARS,

20:02.834 --> 20:04.365
AND I JUST WENT FOR IT,

20:04.367 --> 20:06.132
AND THEY'RE GONNA EITHER SAY
YES OR NO,

20:06.134 --> 20:07.532
BUT IT'S DONE.

20:07.534 --> 20:09.465
WELL, LET'S CELEBRATE.

20:10.800 --> 20:12.465
- GREAT.
- YEAH.

20:12.467 --> 20:15.065
I'M GONNA RUN
TO THE LADIES' ROOM.

20:15.067 --> 20:16.931
OKAY.

20:20.734 --> 20:21.931
HEY, MA, WHAT'S UP?

20:21.933 --> 20:24.265
I THINK
YOU SHOULD COME HOME.

20:24.267 --> 20:25.532
WELL, SORRY, I CAN'T.

20:25.534 --> 20:28.465
KERISSA JUST SHOWED UP
UNEXPECTEDLY,

20:28.467 --> 20:30.265
AND, UH, SHE'S PLANNING
TO TAKE ME OUT.

20:30.267 --> 20:32.265
THERE IS SOMEONE
COMING HOME

20:32.267 --> 20:34.398
THAT I THINK YOU'RE
GONNA WANT TO MEET.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.998
Who?

20:37.000 --> 20:38.532
MARICEL, THE EGG.

20:38.534 --> 20:39.665
YES, PLEASE.

20:39.667 --> 20:41.665
ANYTHING THAT SEEMS
EVEN VAGUELY VALUABLE.

20:41.667 --> 20:42.899
HURRY.
- YES, MA'AM.

20:42.901 --> 20:45.498
MA, WHO'S COMING OVER?

20:45.500 --> 20:47.565
- GRACE'S SON.
- SON?

20:47.567 --> 20:49.665
The whole family's
going to be here.

20:49.667 --> 20:52.231
WOULD YOU PLEASE
JUST COME HOME?

20:52.233 --> 20:53.399
THANK YOU, SON.

20:56.700 --> 20:58.832
WHAT?

20:58.834 --> 20:59.999
CHANGE OF PLANS.

21:00.001 --> 21:01.532
NO. NO, IT'S MY PLAN.

21:01.534 --> 21:04.465
I GET TO SAY WHEN IT CHANGES,
AND I HAVEN'T, SO...

21:04.467 --> 21:05.699
MAMA WANTS US
TO COME HOME.

21:05.701 --> 21:07.465
WELL, SHE IS GOING
TO BE DISAPPOINTED.

21:07.467 --> 21:09.299
GRACE HAS A SON.

21:09.301 --> 21:10.765
WHAT DOES THAT
EVEN MEAN?

21:10.767 --> 21:12.265
I DON'T KNOW,

21:12.267 --> 21:13.998
BUT I THINK WE NEED
TO GET OVER THERE AND FIND OUT.

21:14.000 --> 21:15.965
JACOB,
I'M YOUR WIFE.

21:15.967 --> 21:17.365
WE'RE PUTTING AN OFFER IN
ON THE HOUSE

21:17.367 --> 21:19.732
CAN YOU JUST PUT ME FIRST
FOR ONCE?

21:19.734 --> 21:20.832
I DON'T EVEN UNDERSTAND

21:20.834 --> 21:22.398
HOW YOU MADE THIS OFFER,
FOUND THE MONEY...

21:22.400 --> 21:28.665
JACOB, CAN YOU JUST MAN UP
AND BE MY HUSBAND FOR ONCE?

21:28.667 --> 21:31.132
YOU HAVE GOT FIRED
FROM BOTH OF YOUR JOBS.

21:31.134 --> 21:33.131
I'M NOT COMPLAINING.
I'M NOT LEAVING.

21:33.133 --> 21:34.331
WHERE WOULD YOU GO?

21:34.333 --> 21:37.065
ARE YOU COMING
OR NOT?

21:37.067 --> 21:40.099
NO, I'M GOING HOME
SO I CAN MEET THIS NEPHEW

21:40.101 --> 21:42.832
OR WHOEVER THIS MYSTERY MAN
IS MAMA'S TALKING ABOUT.

21:42.834 --> 21:45.498
I MEAN, ARE YOU COMING WITH ME?

21:45.500 --> 21:49.231
DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I'M COMING?

22:03.900 --> 22:07.398
HI.
THE CHECK CLEARED.

22:07.400 --> 22:10.398
YES, IT DID.

22:10.400 --> 22:11.932
MM-HMM.

22:13.067 --> 22:15.998
UM, I WAS WONDERING...

22:17.334 --> 22:19.198
IF YOU'RE FREE OR...

22:19.200 --> 22:25.465
♪♪

22:31.134 --> 22:32.798
James:

22:34.667 --> 22:36.265
OH!

22:36.267 --> 22:38.932
A.J.

22:38.934 --> 22:40.865
WELCOME TO THE FAMILY.

22:40.867 --> 22:41.998
THANK YOU.

22:42.000 --> 22:44.665
AND, UH, THIS IS MY FATHER,
THE BISHOP.

22:44.667 --> 22:47.132
NOW, I'M SHAKING
OUT OF CEREMONY,

22:47.134 --> 22:48.932
BUT, AT SOME POINT,
I MIGHT WANT TO TAKE HOLD OF IT.

22:48.934 --> 22:49.934
COME HERE.

22:54.400 --> 22:56.998
- WHAT A REVELATION.
- YEAH?

22:57.000 --> 23:00.131
BOY, I THINK HE'S GOT
A LOT OF NOAH IN HIM.

23:00.133 --> 23:01.365
DON'T YOU THINK?

23:01.367 --> 23:04.298
GRACE, TOO.
HE'S A PERFECT MIX.

23:08.467 --> 23:10.099
Y'ALL HAVE
A LOVELY HOME.

23:10.101 --> 23:11.765
WELL, IT'S A WORK
IN PROGRESS.

23:11.767 --> 23:13.665
LOOKS KIND OF FINISHED
TO ME.

23:13.667 --> 23:15.265
WELL,
IT CAN SEEM THAT WAY,

23:15.267 --> 23:16.798
AND THEN SOMETHING NEW
COMES ALONG

23:16.800 --> 23:19.699
AND YOU REALIZE
THE JOURNEY CONTINUES.

23:19.701 --> 23:23.499
- MOM IS A PREACHER, TOO.
- I KIND OF CAUGHT THAT, YEAH.

23:25.300 --> 23:29.798
OH, HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO MEET YOUR COUSIN, ZORA?

23:29.800 --> 23:32.798
SHE'S RIGHT DOWN THE HILL
AT HER LITTLE HIPPIE BUNGALOW,

23:32.800 --> 23:36.098
AND I TOLD HER THAT
WE WERE HAVING YOU OVER.

23:36.100 --> 23:38.565
Y-YEAH I GUESS I WOULD LIKE
THAT VERY MUCH.

23:38.567 --> 23:41.365
GOOD. WELL, THEN,
I'M GONNA WALK YOU DOWN THERE,

23:41.367 --> 23:44.132
AND THAT'LL GIVE US A CHANCE
TO GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

23:48.300 --> 23:49.899
HOW ARE YOU FARING
IN ALL THIS?

23:51.867 --> 23:54.865
IT'S...
IT'S A LOT.

23:54.867 --> 23:58.465
YOU KNOW, YOUR MOTHER
AND I ARE THERE FOR YOU.

23:58.467 --> 23:59.898
WE COULD'VE HELPED
WITH THIS.

23:59.900 --> 24:00.900
I KNOW.

24:02.067 --> 24:03.599
EXCUSE ME.

24:07.800 --> 24:09.931
YEAH?

24:09.933 --> 24:12.998
YES, ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

24:13.000 --> 24:15.465
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

24:15.467 --> 24:18.065
THAT WAS MUILLARD.

24:18.067 --> 24:20.332
THERE'S A DETECTIVE ELLIS
HERE TO SEE YOU

24:20.334 --> 24:22.065
WITH SOME
FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS.

24:27.534 --> 24:29.332
YES?

24:30.534 --> 24:32.299
YEAH, COMING.
COMING, COMING, COMING.

24:33.667 --> 24:34.865
- YOU GOOD?
- YEAH.

24:34.867 --> 24:37.598
ALRIGHT.

24:37.600 --> 24:39.865
A.J., THIS IS YOUR COUSIN,
ZORA.

24:39.867 --> 24:41.198
HEY.

24:41.200 --> 24:42.865
HEY.

24:42.867 --> 24:45.065
BRING IT IN.

24:45.067 --> 24:46.598
IS THIS WHY SOPHIA
WAS SO...

24:46.600 --> 24:48.598
I THINK SO, YES.

24:48.600 --> 24:49.798
Zora: WELL,
YOU ARE ABOUT TO EXPERIENCE

24:49.800 --> 24:52.598
ONE OF THE ALL-TIME FREAK-OUT
CARNIVAL SIDESHOWS

24:52.600 --> 24:53.998
LIFE HAS TO OFFER.

24:54.000 --> 24:55.532
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

24:55.534 --> 24:57.398
GREENLEAF FAMILY DINNER.

24:57.400 --> 24:58.598
- OH.
- OH.

24:58.600 --> 25:01.198
SHE MIGHT BE RIGHT
ABOUT THAT.

25:01.200 --> 25:02.798
COME ON. I'LL GIVE YOU
ALL THE BACKGROUND,

25:02.800 --> 25:04.465
SHOW YOU WHERE
THE LIFE PRESERVERS ARE.

25:04.467 --> 25:06.732
AND IN CASE THERE IS A LOSS
IN CABIN PRESSURE,

25:06.734 --> 25:08.765
A MASK WILL FALL
FROM ABOVE.

25:08.767 --> 25:11.165
ALRIGHT, SO Y'ALL COME UP
IN 10 MINUTES.

25:11.167 --> 25:12.632
OKAY. YES, MA'AM.

25:16.067 --> 25:18.165
SO, A.J...

25:21.834 --> 25:23.098
WANT TO GET HIGH?

25:23.100 --> 25:24.998
JUST A LITTLE.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.731
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE A CHRISTIAN.

25:26.733 --> 25:31.165
I'M CHRISTIAN.
I'M NOT CRAZY.

25:31.167 --> 25:33.865
AND YOU TWO TALKED ABOUT,
WHAT, GOD?

25:36.767 --> 25:38.032
AND EMPLOYMENT.

25:38.034 --> 25:39.432
HE'S LOOKING FOR A JOB.

25:39.434 --> 25:40.898
IT'S NOT AN EASY THING
TO DO.

25:40.900 --> 25:42.332
WELL, WITH HIS RECORD,
IT WOULDN'T BE.

25:42.334 --> 25:43.732
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE,
OFFICER?

25:43.734 --> 25:45.965
YEAH,
JUST ONE LAST THING.

25:45.967 --> 25:48.098
WE HAVE SECURITY FOOTAGE OF YOU
TALKING TO YOUR SON

25:48.100 --> 25:49.165
WHEN YOU GOT TO THE STATION.

25:49.167 --> 25:50.399
AND THERE'S NO AUDIO,

25:50.401 --> 25:52.799
BUT IT'S PRETTY CLEAR
HE WAS ASKING YOU FOR SOMETHING.

25:52.801 --> 25:56.431
MY GUESS IS IT WAS AN ALIBI.
OR AM I MISTAKEN?

25:56.433 --> 25:59.265
LOOK, IF YOU HAD ENOUGH
EVIDENCE TO CONVICT MY SON,

25:59.267 --> 26:00.998
I ASSUME YOU'D HAVE
CHARGED HIM BY NOW.

26:01.000 --> 26:02.365
MY GUESS IS YOU DON'T.

26:02.367 --> 26:05.165
MY GUESS IS HE'S JUST
A BLACK KID UNLUCKY ENOUGH

26:05.167 --> 26:06.898
TO BE WALKING
THE STREETS OF MEMPHIS

26:06.900 --> 26:07.832
WHILE YOU COPS ARE OUT THERE

26:07.834 --> 26:09.232
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE
TO BLAME IT ON.

26:09.234 --> 26:10.899
SO IF YOU HAVE...

26:10.901 --> 26:13.065
GET ACQUAINTED,
AND I HAVE TO SAY THAT...

26:15.767 --> 26:17.098
WHO'S THIS?

26:17.100 --> 26:19.399
DETECTIVE ELLIS, MA'AM,
MEMPHIS P.D.

26:19.401 --> 26:21.132
CHARMED.

26:21.134 --> 26:23.265
I JUST STOPPED BY TO ASK
YOUR DAUGHTER A FEW QUESTIONS

26:23.267 --> 26:25.665
ABOUT A STATEMENT
SHE GAVE EARLIER

26:25.667 --> 26:27.099
ABOUT YOUR GRANDSON.

26:28.934 --> 26:31.998
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH,
MOM.

26:32.000 --> 26:40.000
♪♪

26:40.667 --> 26:41.932
GRACE,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:41.934 --> 26:43.699
WHY HAVE YOU
NOT TOLD ME NOW?

26:51.767 --> 26:53.298
UGH, THAT MAN.

26:53.300 --> 26:56.132
I MEAN, I-I FOUND THE HOUSE,
I FOUND THE MONEY,

26:56.134 --> 26:59.465
AND ALL I ASKED WAS THAT HE
TAKE ME OUT TO CELEBRATE

26:59.467 --> 27:01.665
JUST ONE NIGHT.

27:01.667 --> 27:03.465
HE CAN'T EVEN
TELL HIS MAMA NO.

27:03.467 --> 27:05.065
- MM.
- FOR ONE NIGHT, JUST ONE NIGHT.

27:05.067 --> 27:07.998
I MEAN,
YOU THINK THAT'S RIGHT?

27:08.000 --> 27:09.332
MNH-MNH.

27:10.867 --> 27:16.332
♪♪

27:16.334 --> 27:18.265
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:18.267 --> 27:19.732
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING.

27:19.734 --> 27:27.734
♪♪

27:28.134 --> 27:36.134
♪♪

27:36.400 --> 27:44.400
♪♪

27:44.667 --> 27:52.667
♪♪

27:59.267 --> 28:01.332
SO, THE SQUIRREL
IS DEAD.

28:01.334 --> 28:02.798
James:
THE SQUIRREL IS NOT DEAD.

28:02.800 --> 28:04.465
WELL, IT FEELS
PRETTY DEAD TO ME.

28:04.467 --> 28:05.865
WHAT SQUIRREL
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT?

28:05.867 --> 28:07.465
MY CHURCH, MY FUTURE,

28:07.467 --> 28:09.198
THE WHOLE
MISBEGOTTEN ADVENTURE...

28:09.200 --> 28:10.132
IT'S ALL DEAD.

28:10.134 --> 28:11.999
THEY CAN'T PROVE
THAT I LIED, MAMA.

28:12.001 --> 28:14.132
NO,<i> THEY</i> CAN'T,
BUT <i> HE</i> CAN.

28:14.134 --> 28:15.265
WHO CAN?

28:15.267 --> 28:17.298
A.J.

28:17.300 --> 28:19.665
GRACE,
IF HE EVER CONFESSES...

28:19.667 --> 28:21.965
WHY WOULD HE CONFESS?
HE DIDN'T DO IT.

28:21.967 --> 28:24.932
- BUT WHAT IF HE DID?
- HE DIDN'T.

28:24.934 --> 28:27.998
GRACE, LORD,
HASN'T HE MADE IT CLEAR TO YOU

28:28.000 --> 28:29.532
THAT HE'S NOT
TRUSTWORTHY?

28:29.534 --> 28:32.431
YOU GIVE HIM MONEY.
HE WANTS MORE.

28:32.433 --> 28:34.931
YOU DON'T GIVE IT TO HIM,
AND THEN HE THREATENS YOU.

28:34.933 --> 28:36.665
WHAT IS TO KEEP HIM
FROM EXTORTING

28:36.667 --> 28:38.398
EVERY PENNY WE HAVE
OVER THIS.

28:38.400 --> 28:39.932
UGH, THAT'S INSANE.

28:39.934 --> 28:42.432
SHALL WE...
TO THE MESS HALL?

28:45.001 --> 28:48.332
A.J., WOULD YOU SIT
FOR A MOMENT?

28:50.534 --> 28:51.534
YES, MA'AM.

28:54.534 --> 28:56.499
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

28:56.501 --> 28:58.565
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE FINE.

28:58.567 --> 29:02.031
UH, ZORA,
EXCUSE US, PLEASE.

29:02.033 --> 29:03.031
WHAT ABOUT DINNER?

29:03.033 --> 29:04.565
ZORA.

29:04.567 --> 29:05.665
YES MA'AM.

29:11.534 --> 29:13.199
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:17.301 --> 29:19.065
THE POLICE CAME BY.

29:19.067 --> 29:20.399
ABOUT ME?

29:20.401 --> 29:23.431
YOU SEE,
THAT LOOK RIGHT THERE.

29:23.433 --> 29:24.498
MAMA.

29:24.500 --> 29:25.832
WHAT LOOK? WHAT?

29:25.834 --> 29:26.965
THAT GUILTY LOOK.

29:26.967 --> 29:28.732
A.J., DID YOU DO IT?

29:28.734 --> 29:34.098
LADY, I JUST GOT OUT OF JAIL
AFTER FIVE YEARS.

29:34.100 --> 29:35.465
I'M NOT GOING BACK.

29:35.467 --> 29:37.198
THAT'S NOT ANSWERING
MY QUESTION.

29:37.200 --> 29:38.265
YEAH, IT IS.

29:38.267 --> 29:39.732
YOU KNOW HOW STUPID
I WOULD HAVE TO BE

29:39.734 --> 29:41.398
TO PULL SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

29:41.400 --> 29:44.665
THEY GET ME FOR THAT,
I'M DOING 20, 30 YEARS.

29:44.667 --> 29:47.965
DID YOU DO IT OR NOT?

29:47.967 --> 29:49.999
BECAUSE I'M NOT GONNA LET
THIS DAUGHTER OF MINE

29:50.001 --> 29:54.932
EVEN GET A STAIN ON HER DRESS
DOING SOME CRIMINAL A FAVOR.

29:54.934 --> 29:57.365
GRACE, THERE IS TOO MUCH
ON THE LINE.

29:57.367 --> 29:59.498
MAMA, BACK OFF.

29:59.500 --> 30:01.132
WELL, HE'S NOT ANSWERING
MY QUESTION.

30:01.134 --> 30:02.398
YES, HE DID.

30:02.400 --> 30:04.065
AND DIDN'T YOU SAY YOU DIDN'T
WANT PEOPLE TO FIND OUT?

30:04.067 --> 30:07.465
I DON'T CARE AT THIS POINT
WHAT THEY FIND OUT ABOUT <i> HIM.</i>

30:07.467 --> 30:09.265
I JUST WANT <i> YOU</i>
TO BE SPOTLESS ENOUGH

30:09.267 --> 30:11.532
THAT YOU CAN DO
WHAT WE NEED TO DO...

30:11.534 --> 30:13.132
WHAT, TO GET YOU
BACK YOUR CHURCH?

30:13.134 --> 30:14.532
IS THAT NOT THE MISSION?

30:14.534 --> 30:16.298
THIS IS MY SON.

30:16.300 --> 30:18.932
HE IS INNOCENT.

30:18.934 --> 30:20.465
THEN LET HIM SAY SO.

30:20.467 --> 30:23.265
- A.J.
- YES SIR.

30:23.267 --> 30:25.265
FOR THE SAKE OF THIS WOMAN
WHO WAS ONCE MY WIFE

30:25.267 --> 30:28.465
AND WHO I STILL HOLD
IN THE HIGHEST REGARD,

30:28.467 --> 30:31.498
COULD YOU PLEASE
JUST ANSWER THE QUESTION?

30:31.500 --> 30:32.632
WHICH ONE?

30:32.634 --> 30:34.232
"WHICH ONE?" HM.

30:36.467 --> 30:38.699
SON, DID YOU ROB
THAT DRUGSTORE?

30:42.100 --> 30:44.799
- I THOUGHT WE WERE FAMILY.
- WE ARE.

30:44.801 --> 30:46.865
AND THAT IS WHY
YOU ARE GOING TO SUFFER

30:46.867 --> 30:50.065
MORE THAN YOU EVER HAVE
IN YOUR WHOLE LIFE

30:50.067 --> 30:52.932
IF YOU DON'T MAN UP
AND TELL YOUR FAMILY THE TRUTH.

30:52.934 --> 30:55.198
OKAY, WE'RE GETTING YOU
OUT OF HERE. LET'S GO.

30:55.200 --> 30:58.331
- WHERE IS THIS NEPHEW OF MINE?
- RIGHT THERE.

30:58.333 --> 31:00.532
WELL, GET OVER HERE.
LET ME GIVE YOU A HUG.

31:00.534 --> 31:04.165
COME ON.
COME TO AUNT CHARITY.

31:04.167 --> 31:05.965
SHE BETTER HANG ON
TO HER BAG.

31:05.967 --> 31:07.865
MAE, CAN WE PLEASE
JUST MOVE ON?

31:07.867 --> 31:09.465
I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR
ALL ABOUT YOU.

31:09.467 --> 31:12.865
THERE IS NOTHING
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

31:12.867 --> 31:14.998
- "IT'S A BOY"?
- WELL I ASKED IF THEY HAD

31:15.000 --> 31:18.598
ANY "IT'S A MAN THAT YOUR SISTER
KEPT SECRET FOR 25 YEARS,"

31:18.600 --> 31:20.099
BUT THEY WERE OUT.

31:24.067 --> 31:28.765
A.J., WOULD YOU ANSWER
THE QUESTION?

31:28.767 --> 31:30.932
Jacob: SO, WHERE'S
THIS NEPHEW OF MINE?

31:30.934 --> 31:32.632
HE'S RIGHT HERE.

31:32.634 --> 31:34.232
KERISSA COULDN'T MAKE IT?

31:34.234 --> 31:37.198
UH, NO, SHE'S OUT SOMEWHERE
CELEBRATING.

31:37.200 --> 31:40.532
HEY. I'M JACOB.

31:40.534 --> 31:41.798
AND YOU ARE?

31:41.800 --> 31:45.165
THIS IS GRACE'S SON, JACOB,
A.J.

31:45.167 --> 31:46.665
SINCE WHEN?

31:46.667 --> 31:49.332
SINCE 25 YEARS AGO,
BUT THAT'S ALL IN THE PAST

31:49.334 --> 31:52.599
AND NOW WE JUST WANT
TO HEAR THE STORIES.

31:52.601 --> 31:54.398
Mae: WELL, THERE'S ONE STORY
I WANT TO HEAR,

31:54.400 --> 31:56.465
AND I'M GOING TO HEAR IT.

31:56.467 --> 31:58.531
I'VE GOT NOTHING
TO SAY TO YOU.

31:58.533 --> 32:02.665
A.J.,
YOU DON'T KNOW ME YET,

32:02.667 --> 32:05.332
BUT I AM FORMIDABLE.

32:05.334 --> 32:07.732
I AM
A FORMIDABLE ADVERSARY,

32:07.734 --> 32:09.932
AND I'M EVEN MORE SO
AS A FRIEND,

32:09.934 --> 32:13.765
MORE USEFUL TO YOU THAN RICHES
AND MORE TRUSTWORTHY

32:13.767 --> 32:16.598
THAN THE GROUND
YOU ARE STANDING ON.

32:16.600 --> 32:21.532
I DON'T CARE IF, IN PRISON,
YOU... WITH KILLERS.

32:21.534 --> 32:25.065
YOU HAVE NEVER MET ANYBODY
MORE FORMIDABLE THAN ME.

32:25.067 --> 32:27.231
OKAY,
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

32:27.233 --> 32:32.165
I AM TRYING TO GIVE THIS CHILD
HIS CHANCE.

32:32.167 --> 32:34.165
DID YOU DO IT OR NOT?

32:34.167 --> 32:41.299
♪♪

32:41.301 --> 32:48.598
♪♪

32:48.600 --> 32:51.598
A.J.
A.J. M-MAMA!

32:51.600 --> 32:54.332
WELL, THERE IT IS.

32:54.334 --> 32:56.765
YOU LIED TO THE POLICE
TO PROTECT YOUR SON.

32:56.767 --> 32:58.098
FINE.

32:58.100 --> 33:00.798
AND BEING A MOTHER WHO
SUFFERED SIMILAR INDIGNITIES,

33:00.800 --> 33:01.998
I FEEL FOR YOU.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.000
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

33:04.534 --> 33:06.932
GIGI, AS A CHRISTIAN...

33:06.934 --> 33:09.665
AND AS A MEMBER OF YOUR
CHURCH, I AM IMPLORING YOU.

33:09.667 --> 33:13.599
YOU GO DOWN TO THAT STATION,
AND YOU TELL THEM THE TRUTH.

33:36.800 --> 33:38.332
WHERE YOU BEEN?

33:38.334 --> 33:40.365
I MET WITH NADINE.

33:44.734 --> 33:47.465
WHERE YOU GOING
SO LATE?

33:47.467 --> 33:49.065
CALVARY.

33:49.067 --> 33:51.132
NEED TO GET BACK OVER
TO THE CHURCH FOR SOMETHING.

33:51.134 --> 33:54.865
UM, JUST WAITING ON YOU
TO GET HOME 'CAUSE OF WINKIE.

33:54.867 --> 33:56.798
WELL,
YOU COULD'VE CALLED ME.

33:56.800 --> 34:00.931
COULD I?
DIDN'T SEEM THAT WAY.

34:00.933 --> 34:04.465
I JUST WANTED
TO BE HAPPY, JACOB.

34:04.467 --> 34:10.264
I WANTED US, YOU AND ME,
TO BE HAPPY FOR ONE NIGHT.

34:10.266 --> 34:11.797
YOU HAD A FEW, HUH?

34:11.800 --> 34:13.697
IT WAS A CELEBRATION.

34:13.699 --> 34:14.898
AND BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

34:14.900 --> 34:17.165
I SPENT MOST OF IT
WISHING YOU WERE THERE.

34:23.967 --> 34:25.431
WHAT DID I MISS?

34:27.634 --> 34:29.831
I'LL TELL YOU
IN THE MORNING.

34:31.699 --> 34:36.965
♪♪

34:36.967 --> 34:42.032
♪♪

34:43.934 --> 34:51.864
♪♪

34:53.734 --> 35:01.734
♪♪

35:02.867 --> 35:10.867
♪♪

35:13.934 --> 35:21.934
♪♪

35:23.067 --> 35:24.665
WHAT,
YOU BROUGHT THE COPS?

35:29.667 --> 35:32.798
YOU'RE LEAVING?

35:32.800 --> 35:34.565
THAT'S THE PLAN.

35:34.567 --> 35:36.532
YOU KNOW IT'S GONNA
VIOLATE YOUR PAROLE.

35:36.534 --> 35:38.732
THAT'S THE LEAST
OF MY PROBLEMS.

35:38.734 --> 35:40.532
WHERE YOU PLANNING
ON GOING?

35:40.534 --> 35:41.999
I'M NOT SURE.
I JUST GOT TO GO.

35:42.001 --> 35:43.131
A.J.

35:43.133 --> 35:44.199
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE TRYING TO HELP

35:44.201 --> 35:46.232
AND TRYING TO DO RIGHT
BY BOTH OF US

35:46.234 --> 35:48.665
AND MAYBE THAT GUY
WAS RIGHT... AARON?

35:48.667 --> 35:50.198
MAYBE YOU ARE
A GOOD PERSON,

35:50.200 --> 35:52.065
BUT THIS WHOLE THING
WAS A MISTAKE, OKAY?

35:52.067 --> 35:54.665
YOU SHOULD HAVE NEVER
GOTTEN PREGNANT BY NOAH.

35:54.667 --> 35:56.698
I SHOULD'VE NEVER
HAVE REACHED OUT TO YOU.

35:56.700 --> 35:58.298
YOU SHOULD'VE NEVER
INVITED ME TO MEMPHIS.

35:58.300 --> 35:59.731
- NO.
- I SHOULD'VE NEVER HAVE CAME.

35:59.733 --> 36:00.798
IT WAS ALL A MISTAKE.

36:00.800 --> 36:02.898
WE SHOULD JUST BOTH
CUT OUR LOSSES AND GO.

36:02.900 --> 36:04.731
LET IT GO.
- LOOK AT ME.

36:04.733 --> 36:09.265
DON'T YOU WANT A FAMILY,
HONEY, AFTER ALL THIS TIME?

36:09.267 --> 36:11.399
DON'T YOU WANT A FAMILY?

36:12.600 --> 36:14.499
THAT FAMILY?

36:16.267 --> 36:17.332
NO.

36:19.734 --> 36:23.398
IF YOU LEAVE LIKE THIS, THEY'RE
GONNA THINK YOU'RE GUILTY.

36:23.400 --> 36:26.832
I STOPPED CARING WHAT PEOPLE
THINK ABOUT ME A LONG TIME AGO.

36:29.101 --> 36:30.898
WAIT.
W-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,

36:30.900 --> 36:32.898
WAIT, WAIT
- WHAT? WHAT?

36:32.900 --> 36:34.599
HERE.

36:34.601 --> 36:35.832
TAKE MY CAR.

36:37.600 --> 36:38.932
TAKE GOOD CARE
OF YOURSELF.

36:47.900 --> 36:49.198
YOU DO THE SAME.

36:54.134 --> 37:01.532
♪♪

37:01.534 --> 37:08.898
♪♪

37:08.900 --> 37:16.398
♪♪

37:18.934 --> 37:21.598
DON'T YOU EVER GO HOME?

37:21.600 --> 37:23.465
WHEN THE WORK'S DONE HERE.

37:25.134 --> 37:27.665
SO, WHAT DO YOU HAVE
FOR ME?

37:27.667 --> 37:29.699
STAND UP.

37:29.701 --> 37:31.765
NO, NO, NO.
I'M NOT DOING THAT AGAIN, NO.

37:31.767 --> 37:33.699
NO, JUST STAND UP.

37:33.701 --> 37:35.031
I'M GONNA WANT
A GREAT, BIG HUG

37:35.033 --> 37:36.498
AFTER I FINISH
TELLING YOU THIS,

37:36.500 --> 37:39.365
SO I'M MAKING SURE
YOU'RE READY.

37:39.367 --> 37:40.765
OH, BOY.

37:40.767 --> 37:41.767
OKAY.

37:44.134 --> 37:45.599
GO.

37:45.601 --> 37:47.731
I MET GRACE'S SON.

37:47.733 --> 37:49.065
AND?

37:49.067 --> 37:50.932
AND RIGHT BEFORE

37:50.934 --> 37:53.732
HE WAS SUPPOSED TO MEET
THE FAMILY FOR DINNER,

37:53.734 --> 37:57.831
HE WAS ARRESTED
AS A SUSPECT IN A ROBBERY.

37:57.833 --> 38:00.032
OKAY.
NOW, THAT'S SOMETHING.

38:00.034 --> 38:01.965
OH, JUST WAIT.

38:01.967 --> 38:05.499
GRACE WAS HIS ALIBI,
SO THEY LET HIM GO,

38:05.501 --> 38:08.898
BUT SHE'S LYING.

38:08.900 --> 38:09.965
SHE LIED TO THE COPS?

38:09.967 --> 38:12.098
MM-HMM.

38:12.100 --> 38:13.432
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

38:13.434 --> 38:15.298
I JUST KNOW.

38:15.300 --> 38:16.832
WELL, WE NEED PROOF.

38:20.867 --> 38:22.265
BOOYAH.

38:23.933 --> 38:27.865
WHAT, YOU...
YOU RECORDED HER SAYING IT?

38:27.867 --> 38:29.865
I RECORDED HER
SAYING IT.

38:32.134 --> 38:34.365
OH, THIS DESERVES
MORE THAN A HUG.

38:34.367 --> 38:36.232
THIS IS AMAZING.

38:38.167 --> 38:40.098
JUST PROMISE ME
SOMETHING.

38:40.100 --> 38:41.165
WHAT?

38:41.167 --> 38:43.998
THAT WE CAN USE THIS
TO GET GRACE OUT

38:44.000 --> 38:46.132
WITHOUT SENDING THAT BOY
BACK TO PRISON.

38:46.134 --> 38:48.132
I DON'T EVEN CARE
IF HE DID IT.

38:48.134 --> 38:49.632
HE'S BEEN THROUGH ENOUGH.

38:52.200 --> 38:54.065
I PROMISE.

38:56.867 --> 38:58.931
YOU ARE A GOOD MAN.

38:58.933 --> 39:01.198
AND YOU ARE BEAUTIFUL.

39:01.200 --> 39:09.200
♪♪

39:09.600 --> 39:17.600
♪♪

39:18.000 --> 39:26.000
♪♪

39:26.467 --> 39:30.131
IT'S ALL
GONNA BE OKAY.

39:30.133 --> 39:32.698
I FEEL CERTAIN
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

39:32.700 --> 39:34.765
YOU KNOW, ONE TIME,
I HAD A FRIEND

39:34.767 --> 39:38.665
WHO SAID,
"I GOT A GAL FOR YOU,

39:38.667 --> 39:39.965
AND YOU'RE GONNA
LOVE HER."

39:39.967 --> 39:41.765
AND FOR WEEKS AND WEEKS
BEFORE WE'D MET,

39:41.767 --> 39:45.398
I PICTURED HER,
THIS TOTAL STRANGER.

39:45.400 --> 39:50.032
SAW US HOLDING HANDS,
WALKING TOGETHER.

39:50.034 --> 39:52.898
WHEN I FINALLY DID
MEET HER, MM,

39:52.900 --> 39:56.132
SHE WAS NOTHING LIKE WHAT I...
WHAT I IMAGINED.

39:56.134 --> 40:00.198
SHE WAS MORE WONDERFUL
THAN ANYTHING I HAD IN MIND,

40:00.200 --> 40:01.798
MORE A PART OF ME
I'D BEEN MISSING

40:01.800 --> 40:05.132
THAN I EVER
COULD'VE GUESSED.

40:10.467 --> 40:13.065
SO WHAT IS YOUR POINT,
JAMES?

40:13.067 --> 40:15.532
WHAT'S TO COME
IS JUST LIKE THAT GIRL.

40:15.534 --> 40:18.065
NOW, WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE IT'S GOING,

40:18.067 --> 40:20.731
BUT IT JUST MIGHT BE BETTER
THAN YOU THINK.

40:20.733 --> 40:22.665
SO WHO WAS THIS STRANGER?

40:22.667 --> 40:24.398
WHO DO YOU THINK?

40:30.534 --> 40:33.598
I BETTER...

40:33.600 --> 40:38.299
OH, I BETTER GO BEFORE
I'M LIABLE TO FALL ASLEEP.

40:38.301 --> 40:41.365
YOU CAN FALL ASLEEP.

40:41.367 --> 40:42.798
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

40:42.800 --> 40:44.399
I'M POSITIVE.

40:46.967 --> 40:49.065
OH, GOODNESS.

40:51.000 --> 40:52.565
MM.

40:53.534 --> 40:54.965
HM.

40:57.600 --> 41:00.265
I SAID
YOU COULD GO TO SLEEP.

41:00.267 --> 41:01.765
I WILL.

41:01.767 --> 41:02.965
IF WHAT YOU SAY IS TRUE,

41:02.967 --> 41:05.831
AND EVERYTHING'S ABOUT
TO GO TO HELL IN A HANDBASKET

41:05.833 --> 41:07.898
I WANT TO ENJOY THIS
WHILE I CAN.

41:07.900 --> 41:15.900
♪♪

41:16.333 --> 41:19.232
MM.

41:24.067 --> 41:25.199
HM.

41:30.067 --> 41:31.998
Charity:

41:32.000 --> 41:40.000
♪♪

